wikibase-management/explain-select-wikib: Click on an item below to select it as the target Wikibase to work against. This will clear any existing schema. After switching to the target Wikibase, you should reconcile your data against it before editing the schema.
wikibase-addition/explain-add-manifest: The manifest should specify a reconciliation service linked to the Wikibase, the reconciliation service will be added to OpenRefine if not added yet.
wikibase-addition/explain-add-manifest-v: Enter the Wikibase manifest's URL (recommended, this is helpful for keeping track of the latest manifest):
wikibase-addition/explain-paste-manifest: Or paste the manifest JSON text directly (manifests for some public Wikibases can be found here, you can also write one yourself according to this tutorial):
wikibase-addition/version-error: Manifest version $1 is not supported. OpenRefine supports manifest versions 1.x and 2.x only.
wikibase-schema/preview-explanation: This tab shows the first edits (out of $1) that will be made once you upload the changes to $3. You can use facets to inspect the edits on particular items.
wikibase-schema/empty-terms: no labels, descriptions or aliases added
wikibase-schema/input-placeholder-for-wi: type item or drag reconciled column
type property or drag reconciled column
type file name or drag reconciled column
type lexeme or drag reconciled column
type form or drag reconciled column
type sense or drag reconciled column
wikibase-schema/entity-or-reconciled-col: type entity or drag reconciled column here
wikibase-schema/file-path-placeholder: Absolute path or URL of the media file to upload
wikibase-schema/wikitext-placeholder: Wiki markup associated with the file
wikibase-schema/unsaved-changes-alt: You have made unsaved changes to your Wikibase schema.
wikibase-schema/save-schema-alt: Save the schema to OpenRefine. The changes will not be uploaded to Wikibase yet.
wikibase-schema/discard-schema-changes-a: Discard the changes made to the schema.
wikibase-schema/incomplete-schema-could-: Your schema is incomplete so it cannot be saved yet.
wikibase-schema/unsaved-warning: You have made unsaved changes to your Wikibase schema. Close anyway?
wikibase-schema/incompatible-site-iri-re: This column is reconciled to the identifier space $1, but this input requires a column reconciled to $2.
wikibase-account/explain-log-in: Logging in to $2 lets you upload edits directly from OpenRefine.
wikibase-account/explain-bot-passwords: You are encouraged to login with bot passwords, see this wiki page to learn how to get one.
wikibase-account/explain-owner-only-cons: You need to register an owner-only consumer here first if you don't have one. See this wiki to learn how to get one.
wikibase-account/explain-password-login: You can also login with your username/password.
wikibase-account/explain-owner-only-cons: You can also login with your owner-only consumer.
wikibase-account/password-remember-me-ti: Your password won't be stored. Don't check this if your computer is public.
wikibase-account/owner-only-consumer-rem: Consumer credentials are stored unencrypted in cookies. Don't check this if your computer is public.
perform-wikibase-edits/review-your-edits: You are about to upload $1 edits to $3. Please check them carefully. Large edit batches should be submitted for bot review first.
perform-wikibase-edits/edit-summary-plac: a few words to describe your edits
perform-wikibase-edits/explain-maxlag: Must be a positive integer. Leave this to the default value unless you know how maxlag works.
perform-wikibase-edits/maxlag-validation: maxlag must be a positive integer
warnings-messages/new-item-created/title: This edit batch will create new {wikibase_name} items.
warnings-messages/new-item-created/body: Please make sure that these items do not exist yet and are suitable for inclusion in Wikidata.
warnings-messages/new-item-without-label: New items created without any label or alias.
You should at least provide one label for new items such as {example_entity}, so that others can understand what the item is about.
warnings-messages/new-item-without-descr: New items created without any description.
Adding descriptions on new items such as {example_entity} will make it easier to disambiguate the items from namesakes.
warnings-messages/new-item-with-deleted-: There is probably something wrong in your schema or project.
warnings-messages/new-item-without-insta: New items created without any type.
You should provide an "instance of" (P31 for Wikidata) or "subclass of" (P279 for Wikidata) statement for each item that you create, such as {example_entity}.
warnings-messages/add-statements-with-in: Values for this property are expected to match the regular expression {regex}, which is not the case for {example_value} added on {example_item_entity}.
warnings-messages/remove-statements-with: If these statements currently exist on {wikibase_name}, this will solve constraint violations.
warnings-messages/missing-inverse-statem: Any {added_property_entity} statement such as the one from {source_entity} to {target_entity} should also be added in reverse with {inverse_property_entity}: in this case, {target_entity} {inverse_property_entity} {source_entity}.
warnings-messages/having-conflicts-with-: Remove the conflicting statements with {property_entity} such as item with property {example_entity}.
warnings-messages/self-referential-state: While not forbidden, self-referential statements are generally suspicious. You have some on {example_entity}.
warnings-messages/unsourced-statements/b: Most statements should have references. You can add them easily in the schema.
warnings-messages/property-found-in-main: You are using {property_entity} as a main statement but it is not designed for that.
warnings-messages/property-found-in-qual: You are using in {property_entity} as a qualifier but it is not designed for that .
warnings-messages/property-found-in-refe: You are using {property_entity} in a reference but it is not designed for that.
warnings-messages/missing-mandatory-qual: Statements using {statement_property_entity} such as the one on {example_item_entity} are missing a mandatory {missing_property_entity} qualifier.
warnings-messages/disallowed-qualifiers/: Statements using {statement_property_entity} such as the one on {example_item_entity} should not have a {disallowed_property_entity} qualifier as they are incompatible.
warnings-messages/single-valued-property: {property_entity} added more than once on the same item.
This property is expected to be used at most once on each item but has been added multiple times on the same item, for instance on {example_entity}.
warnings-messages/difference-of-the-prop: The difference between {source_entity} and {target_entity} is expected to be within the range [{min_value}, {max_value}], but this fails on items such as {example_entity}.
warnings-messages/identical-values-for-d: This property should have distinct values, but the same value was found on {item1_entity} and {item2_entity} for instance.
warnings-messages/no-edit-generated/body: There might be something wrong with your schema.
warnings-messages/no-issue-detected/titl: No issue was detected in your edits.
warnings-messages/no-issue-detected/body: Note that OpenRefine cannot detect all the types of problems Wikibase edits can have.
warnings-messages/multi-valued-property-: {property_entity} should have more than one statement on new items.
This property is expected to have more than one statement on each item but it has single statement, for instance on {example_entity}.
{property_entity} should have more than one statement on existing items.

This property is expected to have more than one statement on each item but it has single statement, for instance on {example_entity}. If the item already has statements with this property in {wikibase_name}, then this warning can be ignored.
warnings-messages/new-item-requires-prop: {property_entity} requires property {added_property_entity} to have certain values.
Property {added_property_entity} doesn't have appropriate values such as on item {example_entity}.
warnings-messages/new-item-requires-cert: This property is expected to have another statement with property {added_property_entity} such as on item {example_entity}.
warnings-messages/existing-item-requires: {property_entity} requires property {added_property_entity} to have certain values.

Property {added_property_entity} doesn't have appropriate values such as on item {example_entity}. If the item already has statements with property {added_property_entity} and with appropriate values in {wikibase_name}, then this warning can be ignored.

This property is expected to have another statement with property {added_property_entity} such as on item {example_entity}. If the item already has statements with property {added_property_entity} in {wikibase_name}, then this warning can be ignored.
warnings-messages/values-should-not-be-u: Invalid value for qualifier {qualifier_entity} on statement {statement_entity}
On items such as {example_entity}, an invalid value for qualifier {qualifier_entity} was supplied on statement {statement_entity}.
warnings-messages/no-references-provided: The property {property_entity} specifically requires at least one reference for its statements.
warnings-messages/ignored-qualifiers/bod: Qualifier values could not be parsed, so they will not be added to the corresponding statements.
warnings-messages/ignored-references/bod: None of their statements could be parsed, so no reference was added.
warnings-messages/monolingual-text-witho: No language provided for monolingual text.
Some label, description, alias or monolingual text value have been skipped because no language was provided. Example value: {example_text}.
warnings-messages/duplicate-whitespace/b: Strings such as {example_string} contain duplicate whitespace.
warnings-messages/non-printable-characte: Strings such as {example_string} contain non-printable characters.
warnings-messages/invalid-identifier-spa: Invalid identifier space for reconciled cells.
Some reconciled cells such as {example_cell} were ignored because they are not reconciled to {expected_site_iri}.
warnings-messages/ignored-language/body: Some language identifiers are invalid, such as {example_value}. See the allowed values.
warnings-messages/ignored-date/body: Some dates are incorrectly formatted, such as {example_value}. See the allowed formats.
warnings-messages/ignored-amount/body: Some amounts are incorrectly formatted, such as {example_value}. See the allowed formats.
warnings-messages/ignored-coordinates/bo: Some coordinates are incorrectly formatted, such as {example_value}. See the allowed formats.
warnings-messages/forbidden-value/body: Items such as {example_value_entity} added on {example_subject_entity} are not allowed as values for {property_entity}.
warnings-messages/bounds-disallowed/body: Values are not expected to have uncertainty bounds, but {example_value} added on {example_item_entity} has some. See the manual to learn how to fix their format.
warnings-messages/values-should-be-integ: Values are expected to be integers, but {example_value} added on {example_item_entity} has a fractional part. See the manual to learn how to fix their format.
warnings-messages/invalid-unit/body: Units such as {unit_entity} used on {example_item_entity} are invalid for {property_entity}.
warnings-messages/no-unit-provided/body: Values such as {example_value} on {example_item_entity} are expected to have units.
warnings-messages/invalid-entity-type/bo: Uses of {property_entity} on items such as {example_entity} are invalid.
warnings-messages/early-gregorian-date/t: Early dates in the Gregorian calendar
warnings-messages/early-gregorian-date/b: Dates earlier than October 1582 (such as in year {example_year}) are unlikely to be expressed using the Gregorian calendar. See the manual to specify the appropriate calendar for your dates.
warnings-messages/item-description-too-l: Description ({lang}) such as {description} on {example_entity} is too long. Its length is {length}, which is more than {max_length}. Descriptions are not full sentences, but small bits of information. In most cases, the proper length is between two and twelve words. See the manual for more information.
warnings-messages/item-description-ident: Both the description ({lang}) and the label ({label_lang}) on {example_entity} are {description}. Description are expected to be more specific than labels. See the manual for more information.
warnings-messages/item-description-end-b: Description ({lang}) such as {description} on {example_entity} ends by a punctuation sign "{punctuation_sign}". Description are not sentences, so the punctuation sign at the end should be avoided. See the manual for more information.
warnings-messages/item-description-begin: Description ({lang}) such as {description} on {example_entity} begins with uppercase letter "{uppercase_letter}". Descriptions begin with a lowercase letter except when uppercase would normally be required or expected. See the manual for more information.

Description ({lang}) such as {description} on {example_entity} begins with article "{article}". Descriptions should not normally begin with initial articles ("a", "an", "the"). See the manual for more information.
warnings-messages/invalid-item-subject/t: Invalid subject identifiers for an item edit
warnings-messages/invalid-item-subject/b: Entity identifiers such as {example} cannot be used as subject for an edit on an item. The subject must be a Qid.
warnings-messages/invalid-mediainfo-subj: Invalid subject identifiers for a media file edit
Entity identifiers such as {example} cannot be used as subject for an edit on a media file. The subject must be a Mid.
warnings-messages/invalid-entity-id-form: Reconciled columns contain invalid entity identifiers, such as {example}.
warnings-messages/invalid-item-id-format: Reconciled columns contain invalid item identifiers, such as {example}. Item identifiers should be Qids.
warnings-messages/new-media-created/body: This batch will upload new media files. Please make sure the files you upload are admissible on this wiki.
warnings-messages/new-media-without-file: Uploading new media files requires supplying a path (or URL) to the file to upload. No path was provided for {example_entity}, for instance.
Uploading new media files requires supplying a file name to be used on the wiki. No file name was provided for {example_entity}, for instance.
warnings-messages/new-media-without-wiki: Uploading new media files requires supplying accompanying wikitext. No wikitext was provided for {example_entity}, for instance.
warnings-messages/duplicate-label-and-de: Identical labels and descriptions in language {lang_code}

It is not allowed for two Wikibase items to have the same labels and descriptions in a given language. For instance, this batch would create {first_example_entity} and {second_example_entity}, both with label {common_label} and description {common_description} in language {lang_code}, which is impossible.
warnings-messages/invalid-file-path/body: Some paths of files to be uploaded are invalid, such as {example_path}. Make sure those are valid absolute paths on the system which runs OpenRefine.
warnings-messages/duplicate-file-names-i: Uploading multiple files to the same file name
The file names provided for the new media files should all be distinct. Some file names, such as {example_filename}, are used for more than one file.
warnings-messages/file-names-already-exi: Naming conflict between new and existing files on the wiki
The file names provided for the new media files should be distinct from any existing file names on the wiki. This is not the case for {example_filename}.
warnings-messages/invalid-characters-in-: Filenames such as {example_filename} contain the character {invalid_character} which cannot be part of file names in a wiki.
warnings-messages/file-name-too-long/tit: File names exceeding the maximum length
warnings-messages/file-name-too-long/bod: File names cannot be longer than {max_length} characters. Some file names in this batch are too long, such as {example_filename}.
warnings-messages/missing-file-name-exte: The file names provided for files to be uploaded must end with a file extension, which is not the case for file names such as <span class="wb-issue-preformat">{example_filename}.
warnings-messages/inconsistent-file-name: Inconsistent extensions between file paths and file names
Some file paths and their corresponding target file name on the wiki have different extensions, such as {example_filepath} and {example_filename}.
warnings-messages/replaced-characters-in: Some special characters in file names will be replaced
The characaters :/\ will be replaced by -. For instance, filename {original} will become {normalized}.
wikibase-statement-settings/no-strategy-: No options for this matching strategy.
wikibase-statement-settings/lax-value-ma: Lax value matching (ignore insignificant differences between values, such as trailing whitespace or rounding differences)
wikibase-statement-settings/discriminati: Comma-delimited list of property identifiers of the qualifiers to take into account when comparing statements. Differences in other qualifiers will be ignored. If the list is empty, all qualifiers are taken into account.
wikibase-statement-settings/mode-options: Add the statement or merge it with the first existing statement that matches it.
Only add the statement if there are no matching statements on the entity. Otherwise, leave those statements untouched.
wikibase-statement-settings/strategy-opt: Compare statements using their property, main value and qualifiers.
Compare statements by their main property and main value only.
Compare statements by their main property only.
wikibase-save-schema-dialog/existing-sch: Or select an existing schema to override
wikibase-save-schema-dialog/empty-name: Please provide a name for the schema.
wikibase-schema/schema-load-erases-schem: This will discard the current schema, which has unsaved changes.
wikibase-schema-management-dialog/enter-: Enter a new name for the schema
